          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "10B target with thickness of 200 mu-g/cm2 was bombarded",
                "by 24Mg ions to produce nuclei of interest 32Cl"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Gamma rays emitted from recoiling heavy nuclei",
                "were detected by Gammasphere, which consisted of 98",
                "Compton suppressed high-purity Ge detectors covering",
                "nearly whole solid angle 4Pi."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Ions recoiling from the target were separated",
                "from the beam and dispersed by the Argonne Fragment",
                "Mass Analyzer, which selects recoils according to",
                "their mass-to-charge ratio."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PGAC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Parallel-grid avalanche counter was located at",
                "the focal plane of the FMA to determine",
                "mass-to-charge ratio of the reaction products by",
                "their measured horizontal positions."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Ions were stopped in an ionization chamber",
                "filled with isobutane gas at 13 Torr. The IC was",
                "divided into three segments (5, 5, and 20 cm long,",
                "respectively) to facilitate particle identification",
                "by energy loss (dE) and total energy (E) measurements."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Excited states in 32Cl nucleus were produced via",
                "nuclear reaction 10B(24Mg,2n)32Cl by bombarding 10B",
                "target with 24Mg ions. Ions recoiling from the target",
                "were separated from the beam and dispersed by the",
                "Argonne Fragment Mass Analyzer"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Excited states of 32Cl were studied by gamma",
                "spectroscopy. The unbound states at 1738.1 and 2130.5",
                "keV in 32Cl correspond to 156 and 549 keV resonances",
                "in the 31S(p,gamma)32Cl reaction and their properties",
                "dominate the 31S(p,gamma)32Cl reaction rate. Gamma-ray",
                "partial widths were inferred based upon properties of",
                "mirror states in 32P"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " E-dE method was used for particle identification"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Coincidence between gamma rays and recoil ions",
                "was required"
              ]
            }
          ],
